<title type="html"><![CDATA[12/22(Sat.) China's staggering 40 years of change &amp; New Year’s Resolutions Are For Losers(Host: Ivonne)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=240&amp;p=254#p254"><![CDATA[
12/22(Sat.) China's staggering 40 years of change in pictures &amp; New Year’s Resolutions Are For Losers — Take These 4 Steps Instead (Host: Ivonne)<br /><br />Article 1 ~~ <br />China's staggering 40 years of change in pictures<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-46602785">https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-46602785</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Discussion ~<br />1)China’s economic goes fast and fast in past three decades , how china be changed ? Have you ever been to China?<br /><br />2)Why the economic transformation still NOT  changes the  China’s one-party system of communist rule? <br /><br />3) Couple days ago, why The Chinese president, Xi Jinping, said <br />“No one is in a position to dictate to the Chinese people what should or should not be done,” Do you agree it?<br /><br />4) China has ended the one-child policy and allows couples to have two children.  There is even speculation that the policy may be relaxed further - to allow three or more children - in the near future. The population of china is more than one billion? Do you think it is a good policy?<br /><br />5)Do you plan moving to China or not , why?<br /><br />Article 2 ~~<br />New Year’s Resolutions Are For Losers — Take These 4 Steps Instead<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/justinconklin/2018/12/18/new-years-resolutions-are-for-loserstake-these-4-steps-instead/#689eddf85e2c">https://www.forbes.com/sites/justinconk ... 9eddf85e2c</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><br />Discussion~~<br />1)Why we need to make a resolutions for the New Year ?<br /><br />2) What would you like your new year to look like?         <br />                                                                                                    <br />3) Don’t Make Rigid Resolutions— what you choose a word to guide your coming year?  How it give you the shape and direction? <br /><br />4) Why the resolutions clearly don’t work for the majority of people ?  Have you experienced the successful resolutions , please share<br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00-7:30 free talk<br />(Session 1)<br />7:30-7:35 Opening remarks/ Newcomers self-introduction/ Grouping<br />7:35~ 8:15 discussion session (40 mins)<br />(Session 2)<br />8:15 ~9:00pm discussion session (45 mins)<br />9:00~9:30 free talk<br /><br />Position: Dante coffee Shop (丹堤咖啡), MRT板南線 - 新埔站2號出口, next to 7-Seven, <br />板橋民生路二段237 號, <br />Time: PM 7:00-9:30, <br />minimum charge of Dante coffee for Royal English club attendant NT$80 (丹提低消80元)<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500.請帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=872">Shuman</a> — Wed Dec 19, 2018 6:39 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
